<section class="manifesto" id="manifesto">
  <div class="manifesto-inner">
    <div class="manifesto-left">
      <div class="section-label">The Problem</div>
      <h2 class="manifesto-headline">Contractors are flying blind.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="manifesto-right">
      <p>A homeowner sends a blurry photo over Facebook Messenger. You drive 45 minutes. The job falls through. That's not a bad day — that's a business model problem.</p>
      <p>Most contractors still use phone calls, text threads, and Facebook DMs to capture work. No photos. No measurements. No project details. Just vibes and hope.</p>
      <p>The contractors who win are the ones who respond fastest — not the ones who show up best.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>